description:
Mankind would not have made the new age, encountering the crisis at the end of the last century, that almost wiped them out... if it weren't for "them".

In 1969, "they" who were still in their youth, created a symbol.

In 1997, as the footsteps of the coming disaster slowly starts to show out, the symbol revives. This is a story about several boys, that save the world.

The "Friend" -- a man who intends to destroy the world, starts to say that the "will of space" has begun to choose who are "true" friends. Then, there were those dreadful incidents --

A mysterious virus, death of a detective, a man on the run... Kenji tries to find out who the "Friend" is... but the answer is still lying far ahead/

The footsteps of doom slowly creep closer, and casts a shadow over the city...

The plot to destruction, that Kenji made up when he was just a boy...

Bacteriological attacks, against San Francisco and London, turn real with the "Friend"'s hands. What will happen next? The only person who knows the only person who can save the world -- is Kenji... Firing up his guitar, and making up his mind to stand up, Kenji, alone, goes to the concert hall where the "Friend" awaits.

Kenji wrote "The Book of Prophecy" in his boyhood days. A simple and meaningless scenario made up then is the base for The "Friend"'s plot to destroy mankind. Kenji seeks chance to fight back. Meanwhile, the evil hands of the mysterious organization close in to a man called "Shogun", living in the ganglands of Bangkok. The mysteries grow deeper, the fear more intense, as we near the final battle at the turn of the century... Is there really any way, to save the world from termination?

While the "Friend" has never been identified as of yet, days pass by moment to moment, counting down to December 31st, 2000.... the day when earth sees it's end. The only ones to save the world are the so-called "nine friends" who've written "The Book of Prophecy" during their boyhoods, will humans ever are able to enter a new world save and sound!?

14 years after the "Bloody New Year's Eve" that plunged the world to the terror of extinction, Neo Tokyo, in the year 2014, has regained its peace and become a prospering metropolis that attracts many races. In the chaos, Kanna has turned 17 years old and just found a terrible truth that may change her destiny in the future. What is the truth!?

10 kilometers away from the urban area, the man was still alive on a fort built in the middle of Tokyo bay!! Who will be the one to bring forth the true peace!?
